{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b1592bc-887e-4675-ba5b-922aa73acd63","content":"Here's the recommended setup for MSTest with parallel-by-default execution and sequential database tests:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.*\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a `.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>          <!-- 0 = use all available cores -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>    <!-- parallelize across methods -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr, equivalently, add this assembly-level attribute (e.g. in a `Usings.cs`):\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.Method)]\n```\n\n## 3. Make database tests sequential\n\nUse `[DoNotParallelize]` on a test class to opt it out:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void InsertOrder_WritesToDb() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void DeleteOrder_RemovesFromDb() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll other `[TestClass]` classes run in parallel. Classes marked `[DoNotParallelize]` run alone — no other test executes concurrently with them.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `Workers = 0` means \"use processor count\" — best default.\n- `Scope = MethodLevel` gives maximum parallelism; use `ClassLevel` if tests within a class share state.\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` can go on a class or individual method.\n- Prefer the `.runsettings` approach if you want CI to override values easily (`dotnet test -s my.runsettings`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"990c5037-15d6-406c-8906-bc3af28a5e91","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no existing codebase here. The user is asking for guidance on setting up an MSTest project from scratch. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.","outputTokens":647,"requestId":"1BCB:C0207:237DF5F:27426BE:6A03DA30"},"id":"9298882f-9ed9-4d81-b10f-df683863e815","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:56:16.109Z","parentId":"19e055be-ed4d-4602-92aa-c11233475944"}
